answers.body_markdown:
The line `p=j;` in the inner loop changes `p`. This causes `p` to be different from `i` later, when `if(a[p]&gt;a[j])` is evaluated with a new `j`.

Your code does not need `p` at all. The test can be merely `if (a[i] &gt; a[j])`, and the code inside the loop can be:

    t = a[i];
    a[i] = a[j];
    a[j] = t;

Looking at your code, it seems you think you needed to record `i` or `j` in `p` temporarily and then use `p`. That is not necessary. To use the values of `i` or `j`, simply use `i` or `j`.

