The `state` or `props` changes can trigger the render. Also `this.forceUpdate();` 

You can do like

     const barWidth = this.getProgressWidth(boundingClientRect)
     this.setState({barWidth: barWidth});

But changing state inside render is not good idea. Because it will trigger infinite rendering process. You should declare one `event` and change `state` in that event. :)

